<article>
    <h1>HAND&#xAD;CRAFTED CAN&#xAD;TONESE PAS&#xAD;TRIES</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210108/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-08"><time>2021-01-08</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | WEEKEND</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>With egg tarts from Tai Cheong Bak­ery and Joy Luck Tea­house avail­able in Sin­ga­pore, do peo­ple re­ally need another con­tender?</p>
    <p>Yes, if they are from Wan Hao Pop-Up, which re­tails hand­crafted Can­tonese pas­tries (left) made by Wan Hao Chi­nese Restau­rant’s culi­nary team.</p>
    <p>The egg tarts are made with free-range eggs. Those that are es­pe­cially in­ter­est­ing are the Yam Egg Tart ($3.50) and the Red Bean Egg Tart ($3.50). The yam ver­sion has a layer of orh nee-like fill­ing – Thai yam cooked with corn oil and sugar – un­der the egg cus­tard. Ja­panese red beans – cooked for over an hour un­til they are ten­der – are used in the red bean ver­sion.</p>
    <p>The Co­conut Egg Tart ($3.50) is not bad too, with shred­ded co­conut lend­ing a crunchy tex­ture that com­ple­ments the creamy egg cus­tard. But the Gula Me­laka Egg Tart ($3.50) does not quite cut it as the fill­ing tastes more of caramel than rich gula me­laka.</p>
    <p>The cookie crust of the egg tarts is thin yet holds up re­mark­ably well.</p>
    <p>Other items worth try­ing are the Baked Char Siew Bun ($3) and Wife Cake or Lao Po Bing ($3). Both come with gen­er­ous fill­ings. The char siew fill­ing for the bun and the win­ter melon fill­ing for the Wife Cake are pre­pared in-house.</p>
    <p>The Chi­nese Wal­nut Cook­ies ($18 for a 200g jar) and Al­mond Cook­ies ($18 for a 200g jar) are crispy. The al­mond cook­ies are par­tic­u­larly ad­dic­tive as they have a melt-in-the-mouth tex­ture.</p>
    <p>Best of all, the pas­tries are not overly sweet.</p>
    <p>WHERE Java+, Level 1 Sin­ga­pore Mar­riott Tang Plaza Ho­tel,</p>
    <p>320 Or­chard Road MRT Or­chard</p>
    <p>OPEN Till Feb 20, 11am to 5pm. Only for walk-in take­away pur­chases; no pre-or­ders avail­able</p>
    <p>TEL Call 6831-4605 for in­quiries</p>


